      <div class="msgContentFrame">It seems you misunderstood me when I said to opt in for overdraft services, or I worded it improperly.  You should be able to change how you want you account handled.  The new laws require that the banks give you the option to decline overdraft practices, but you should still be able to choose to have them enabled.  You should be able to find your overdraft settings online, or by calling or visiting a branch. <br /> <br />Edit: It seems BoA doesn't do it at all on &quot;non-recurring&quot; charges anymore.  Many banks still give you the option to have these charges allowed.  Perhaps you should find another bank that better suits your purposes. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov 16th 2010  4:40pm by Spoonless </span></i></div>
