      <div class="msgContentFrame">how about negotiating different days for bills to be paid?  Most credit cards are willing to move your payment due date if you ask.  Time Warner Cable changed my billing date over the phone. When I had cell phones with both Verizon and Alltel I could change it via their websites. <br /> <br />Also, might want to review your rental agreement--you may actually have a grace period before you are charged a late fee.  This is actualy a requirement for payment agreements in some states because it used to be that bank transactions were not run on the weekends, so payments could not always be paid on the first day of the month.  Might only be one business day or something, but it sounds like you only need 1 day anyway. <br /> <br />Raist</div>
