      <div class="msgContentFrame">You're trying to figure out ways to make everybody else bend over backwards so that your FFXI account gets paid on time every month. All you really have to do to stop FFXI from being shut down on your bank's end is save $14 from a pay check <i>once</i>. Stop buying coffee for a week, or work a single hour of overtime. Take the bus, or ride your bike if you already use transit. Stop buying pop, stop buying junk food, stop buying name brands, don't text as much. Anything, for <i>one single</i> month. Once you switch your payment going in at the beginning of the month from the next paycheck to at the end of the month from the last paycheck, all you have to do is hold off spending that $14 for the rest of your FFXI playing career. Everybody is happy, The End.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Dooom wrote:</div><div class="orig">BG elitists &lt;3 haste. <br /> <br />Allatards/uber casuals hate elitists. <br /> <br />Allatards/uber casuals hate haste, as valuing it would acknowledge that elitists are right</div></div> <br /> <br /><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">kerberoz wrote:</div><div class="orig">People don't hate emo kids because they're &quot;misunderstood.&quot; People hate emo kids because they're useless.</div></div></div></div>
