      <div class="msgContentFrame">Alternatively, you could try using an actual Visa or MasterCard.  I have a Chase/BP Visa that is actually a Gas card with a Visa logo on it.  I originally got it as an Ammoco gas card, it got upgraded to an Ammoco Visa, then they merged with BP and it became a BP Visa, then eventually a Chase BP Visa.  It's always worked for FFXI through all the changes (so long as I updated my payment method with the new numbers/dates each time I got a new card. <br /> <br />Since you have accounts with BOA, might want to look into one of there $500 cards.  I got a $500 card from Wachovia when I turned 18 mostly because I had checking/savings accounts with them since I started working at 16--it was what I started building my credit with.  If you have a good relationship with them, should be able to get a low limit one to use--especially if you go over the issue you are having with the payments going through properly.  Customer Satisfaction is the name of the game right now--doubt they'd want you going to their competition right now when they may have a simple solution in-house. <br /> <br />Worst case scenario, you could go for a BP card or something in the hopes of getting a V/MC card you can use.  They practically give the gas cards away. <br /> <br />Raist</div>
